<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0958 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this review, are described the clinical, morphological and immunologicalfeatures of fatal IM. The clinical and morphological features of sporadicfatal IM are compared with those of fatal IM in the X-linked lympho-proliferativesyndrome (XLP). Since two extensive reviews of the lympho-proliferativediseases that occur in immune-deficient patients have recently been written,only a brief summary of the immune defects found in patients with fatalIM is given.</TEXT></DOC>